  16class NasModule(nn.Module):
  17    def __init__(self, cfg, name: str, input_shape):
  18        """
  19        basic module composing neural networks.
  20        :param cfg: global configuration
  21        :param name: module name
  22        :param input_shape: input data shape
  23        """
  24        super().__init__()
  25        self.logger = get_logger('module', cfg.LOG_FILE)
  26        self.cfg = cfg
  27        self.input_shape = input_shape  # (channel, feature)
  28        self.name = name
  29        self.output_shape = None
  30        self.params = None
  31        self.editable = self.cfg.modulesConfig[name]['editable']
  32        self._module_instance = None  # buffer the instance
  33        self.current_level = None  # current width level
  34        self.widen_sample_fn = self.default_sample_strategy
  35        # add pruning field
  36        if cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
  37            self.importance_score = None  # importance score matrix
  38
  39    @property
  40    @abc.abstractmethod
  41    def is_max_level(self):
  42        """
  43        :return: True if this module is max width level,False otherwise
  44        """
  45        pass
  46
  47    @property
  48    def next_level(self) -> int:
  49        """
  50        :return: width of next level
  51        """
  52        out_range = self.cfg.modulesConfig[self.name]['out_range']
  53        out_range = list(out_range)
  54        valid_range = []
  55        for i in out_range:
  56            if i > self.current_level:
  57                valid_range.append(i)
  58        if len(valid_range) == 0:
  59            return self.current_level
  60        else:
  61            return min(valid_range)
  62
  63    def get_level(self, level_list, max_width) -> int:
  64        """
  65        determine init level, return random level
  66        :param max_width:
  67        :param level_list: all available level list
  68        :return: level
  69        """
  70        if max_width is not None:
  71            level_list = [i for i in level_list if i <= max_width]
  72        return random.sample(level_list, 1)[0]

  74    @abc.abstractmethod
  75    def init_param(self, input_shape, max_width):
  76        """
  77        initialize parameters of this module
  78        :param max_width: max width of neural layer
  79        :return: None
  80        """
  81        pass
  82
  83    def forward(self, x):
  84        return self._module_instance(x)
  85
  86    def on_param_end(self, input_shape):
  87        """
  88        common operation after parameter setting ending, should call at
  89        the end of each subclass's init_param method
  90        :param input_shape: input shape of this module
  91        """
  92        # get output shape
  93        m = self.get_module_instance()
  94        input_data = torch.zeros([1, *input_shape])
  95        output = m(input_data)
  96        self.output_shape = output.shape[1:]
  97        self.input_shape = tuple(self.input_shape)
  98        self.output_shape = tuple(self.output_shape)

 162    @staticmethod
 163    def mask_sanity_check(mask):
 164        """
 165        check if mask makes all neuron deleted, if so, randomly keep 1 neuron to keep network
 166        work properely
 167        """
 168        if mask.any():
 169            return
 170        mask[torch.randint(mask.shape[0], (1,))] = True
 171        assert mask.any()  # keep at least one neuron
 172
 173    @staticmethod
 174    def default_sample_strategy(original_size, new_size):
 175        """
 176        default sample strategy described in paper
 177        :param original_size: original layer width
 178        :param new_size: new layer width, we have new_size >original_size
 179        :return: sampling sequence
 180        """
 181        seq = list(range(original_size))
 182        num_to_sample = new_size - original_size
 183        while num_to_sample != 0:
 184            sample_number = min(original_size, num_to_sample)
 185            seq += random.sample(seq, sample_number)
 186            num_to_sample = num_to_sample - sample_number
 187        return seq

 190class RNNModule(NasModule):
 191
 192    @property
 193    def is_max_level(self):
 194        out_range = self.cfg.modulesConfig['rnn']['out_range']
 195        return self.current_level >= max(out_range)
 196
 197    def init_param(self, input_shape, max_width):
 198        assert len(input_shape) == 2
 199        self.params = dict()
 200        out_range = self.cfg.modulesConfig['rnn']['out_range']
 201        self.current_level = self.get_level(out_range, max_width)
 202        self.params['input_size'] = input_shape[1]
 203        self.params['output_size'] = self.current_level
 204        # get output shape
 205        self.on_param_end(input_shape)
 206        # add pruning field
 207        if self.cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 208            def score_accumulate_hook(module, grad_input, grad_output):
 209                with torch.enable_grad():
 210                    parameter_dict = dict(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.named_parameters())
 211                    weight_mask = ScoreAccumulator.apply(self.importance_score)
 212                    #
 213                    # # manually calculate importance score
 214                    # weight_ih_l0 = \
 215                    #     parameter_dict['weight_ih_l0'] * torch.unsqueeze(weight_mask, 1)
 216                    # weight_hh_l0 = \
 217                    #     parameter_dict['weight_hh_l0'] * torch.unsqueeze(weight_mask, 0) * torch.unsqueeze(weight_mask, 1)
 218                    # bias_ih_l0 = \
 219                    #     parameter_dict['bias_ih_l0'] * weight_mask
 220                    # bias_hh_l0 = \
 221                    #     parameter_dict['bias_hh_l0'] * weight_mask
 222                    #
 223                    # # backward
 224                    # weight_ih_l0.backward(parameter_dict['weight_ih_l0'].grad)
 225                    # weight_hh_l0.backward(parameter_dict['weight_hh_l0'].grad)
 226                    # bias_ih_l0.backward(parameter_dict['bias_ih_l0'].grad)
 227                    # bias_hh_l0.backward(parameter_dict['bias_hh_l0'].grad)
 228
 229            def accumulate_importance(score):
 230                if self.importance_score.grad is None:
 231                    self.importance_score.grad = score
 232                else:
 233                    self.importance_score.grad += score
 234
 235            def weight_ih_hook(grad):
 236                grad_calculated = torch.sum(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.weight_ih_l0 * grad, 1)
 237                accumulate_importance(grad_calculated)
 238                return grad
 239
 240            def weight_hh_hook(grad):
 241                grad_calculated = self._module_instance.rnn_unit.weight_hh_l0 * grad
 242                grad_calculated = torch.sum(grad_calculated, 0) + torch.sum(grad_calculated, 1)
 243                accumulate_importance(grad_calculated)
 244                return grad
 245
 246            def bias_ih_hook(grad):
 247                grad_calculated = self._module_instance.rnn_unit.bias_ih_l0 * grad
 248                accumulate_importance(grad_calculated)
 249                return grad
 250
 251            def bias_hh_hook(grad):
 252                grad_calculated = self._module_instance.rnn_unit.bias_hh_l0 * grad
 253                accumulate_importance(grad_calculated)
 254                return grad
 255
 256            self.importance_score = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(self.current_level))
 257            # self._module_instance.rnn_unit.register_full_backward_hook(score_accumulate_hook)
 258            self._module_instance.rnn_unit.weight_ih_l0.register_hook(weight_ih_hook)
 259            self._module_instance.rnn_unit.weight_hh_l0.register_hook(weight_hh_hook)
 260            self._module_instance.rnn_unit.bias_ih_l0.register_hook(bias_ih_hook)
 261            self._module_instance.rnn_unit.bias_hh_l0.register_hook(bias_hh_hook)
 262
 263    def forward(self, x):
 264        return self._module_instance(x)

 266    @staticmethod
 267    def identity_module(cfg, name, input_shape: tuple):
 268        if type(name) != str:
 269            name = cfg.NASConfig['editable'][name]
 270        module = RNNModule(cfg, name, input_shape)
 271        output_size = input_shape[1]
 272        input_size = input_shape[1]
 273        module.params = {
 274            "output_size": output_size,
 275            "input_size": input_size,
 276        }
 277        module.current_level = output_size
 278        module.output_shape = input_shape
 279        rnn = NAS_RNN(
 280            input_size=input_size,
 281            hidden_size=output_size,
 282            nonlinearity='relu',
 283            batch_first=True,
 284        )
 285        bias_ih_l0 = torch.zeros(output_size)
 286        rnn.rnn_unit.bias_ih_l0 = nn.Parameter(bias_ih_l0, True)
 287        bias_hh_l0 = torch.zeros(output_size)
 288        rnn.rnn_unit.bias_hh_l0 = nn.Parameter(bias_hh_l0, True)
 289        weight_ih_l0 = torch.eye(output_size)
 290        rnn.rnn_unit.weight_ih_l0 = nn.Parameter(weight_ih_l0, True)
 291        weight_hh_l0 = torch.zeros((output_size, output_size))
 292        rnn.rnn_unit.weight_hh_l0 = nn.Parameter(weight_hh_l0, True)
 293        module._module_instance = rnn
 294        if cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 295            module.importance_score = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(module.current_level))
 296        return module
 297
 298    def get_module_instance(self):
 299        if self._module_instance is not None:
 300            return self._module_instance
 301        if self.params is None and self.output_shape is None:
 302            raise ValueError("parameter must be initialized before generate module instance!!!")
 303        self._module_instance = NAS_RNN(
 304            input_size=self.params['input_size'],
 305            hidden_size=self.params['output_size'],
 306            nonlinearity='relu',
 307            batch_first=True,
 308        )
 309        return self._module_instance
 310
 311    @property
 312    def token(self):
 313        return 'rnn-%d' % (self.params['output_size'])
 314
 315    def perform_wider_transformation_current(self):
 316        next_level = self.next_level
 317        new_module_instance = NAS_RNN(
 318            input_size=self.params['input_size'],
 319            hidden_size=next_level,
 320            nonlinearity='relu',
 321            batch_first=True,
 322        )
 323        # keep previous parameters
 324        mapping_g = self.widen_sample_fn(self.current_level, next_level)
 325        scale_g = [1 / mapping_g.count(i) for i in mapping_g]
 326        scale_g = torch.tensor(scale_g)
 327        rnn = new_module_instance.rnn_unit
 328        rnn.bias_ih_l0 = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.bias_ih_l0[mapping_g], True)
 329        rnn.bias_hh_l0 = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.bias_hh_l0[mapping_g], True)
 330        rnn.weight_ih_l0 = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.weight_ih_l0[mapping_g], True)
 331        rnn.weight_hh_l0 = nn.Parameter(
 332            (self._module_instance.rnn_unit.weight_hh_l0[:, mapping_g] * scale_g)[mapping_g], True)
 333        self.current_level = next_level
 334        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 335        self.output_shape = (self.output_shape[0], self.current_level)
 336        self.params['output_size'] = self.current_level
 337        if self.cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 338            self.importance_score = Parameter(self.importance_score[mapping_g])
 339        return mapping_g, scale_g
 340
 341    def perform_wider_transformation_next(self, mapping_g: list, scale_g: list):
 342        next_level = len(mapping_g)
 343        scale_g = torch.tensor(scale_g)
 344        new_module_instance = NAS_RNN(
 345            input_size=next_level,
 346            hidden_size=self.params['output_size'],
 347            nonlinearity='relu',
 348            batch_first=True,
 349        )
 350        rnn = new_module_instance.rnn_unit
 351        rnn.bias_ih_l0 = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.bias_ih_l0, True)
 352        rnn.bias_hh_l0 = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.bias_hh_l0, True)
 353        rnn.weight_ih_l0 = \
 354            nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.weight_ih_l0[:, mapping_g] *
 355                         scale_g.unsqueeze(0),
 356                         requires_grad=True)
 357        rnn.weight_hh_l0 = \
 358            nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.weight_hh_l0,
 359                         requires_grad=True)
 360        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 361        self.input_shape = (self.input_shape[0], next_level)
 362        self.params['input_size'] = next_level
 363
 364    def perform_prune_current(self, mask):
 365        """
 366        prune rnn layer by output neuron
 367        @param mask:
 368        """
 369        self.mask_sanity_check(mask)  # ensure mask legal
 370        self.current_level = mask.sum().item()
 371        new_module_instance = NAS_RNN(
 372            input_size=self.params['input_size'],
 373            hidden_size=self.current_level,
 374            nonlinearity='relu',
 375            batch_first=True,
 376        )
 377
 378        # keep previous parameters
 379        rnn = new_module_instance.rnn_unit
 380        rnn.bias_ih_l0 = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.bias_ih_l0[mask])
 381        rnn.bias_hh_l0 = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.bias_hh_l0[mask])
 382        rnn.weight_ih_l0 = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.weight_ih_l0[mask])
 383        rnn.weight_hh_l0 = nn.Parameter(
 384            (self._module_instance.rnn_unit.weight_hh_l0[:, mask])[mask])
 385        # make all parameters compact
 386        rnn.flatten_parameters()
 387
 388        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 389        self.output_shape = (self.output_shape[0], self.current_level)
 390        self.params['output_size'] = self.current_level
 391        self.importance_score = nn.Parameter(self.importance_score[mask])
 392
 393    def perform_prune_next(self, mask):
 394        input_size = mask.sum().item()
 395        new_module_instance = NAS_RNN(
 396            input_size=input_size,
 397            hidden_size=self.params['output_size'],
 398            nonlinearity='relu',
 399            batch_first=True,
 400        )
 401        rnn = new_module_instance.rnn_unit
 402        rnn.bias_ih_l0 = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.bias_ih_l0, True)
 403        rnn.bias_hh_l0 = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.bias_hh_l0, True)
 404        rnn.weight_ih_l0 = \
 405            nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.weight_ih_l0[:, mask])
 406        rnn.weight_hh_l0 = \
 407            nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.rnn_unit.weight_hh_l0)
 408        # make all parameters compact
 409        rnn.flatten_parameters()
 410        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 411        self.input_shape = (self.input_shape[0], input_size)
 412        self.params['input_size'] = input_size

 415class DenseModule(NasModule):
 416    def perform_prune_current(self, mask):
 417        """
 418        prune dense layer by row, inplace operation
 419        :param mask: mask of pruning, should be equal to row of weight
 420        """
 421        self.mask_sanity_check(mask)  # ensure mask legal
 422        self.current_level = mask.sum().item()
 423        new_module_instance = nn.Linear(self.params['in_features'], self.current_level)
 424
 425        # assigning new attribute
 426        new_module_instance.bias = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.bias[mask])
 427        new_module_instance.weight = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.weight[mask])
 428        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 429        self.output_shape = (self.output_shape[0], self.current_level)
 430        self.params['out_features'] = self.current_level
 431        self.importance_score = nn.Parameter(self.importance_score[mask])
 432
 433    def perform_prune_next(self, mask):
 434        weight = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.weight[:, mask])
 435        self.params['in_features'] = mask.sum().item()
 436        new_module_instance = nn.Linear(self.params['in_features'], self.current_level)
 437        new_module_instance.weight = weight
 438        new_module_instance.bias = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.bias)
 439
 440        # assigning new attribute
 441        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 442        self.input_shape = (self.input_shape[0], self.params['in_features'])
 443
 444    @property
 445    def is_max_level(self):
 446        out_range = self.cfg.modulesConfig['dense']['out_range']
 447        return self.current_level >= max(out_range)
 448
 449    def init_param(self, input_shape, max_width):
 450        assert len(input_shape) == 2
 451        out_range = self.cfg.modulesConfig['dense']['out_range']
 452        in_features = input_shape[1]
 453        self.current_level = self.get_level(out_range, max_width)
 454        self.params = {'in_features': in_features,
 455                       "out_features": self.current_level}
 456        self.on_param_end(input_shape)
 457        # add pruning field
 458        if self.cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 459            self.importance_score = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(self.current_level))
 460
 461    def forward(self, x):
 462        if self.cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 463            # accumulate importance score of whole row, we use this as importance estimation of output neuron
 464            score = self.importance_score
 465            weight_mask = ScoreAccumulator.apply(score)  # no change
 466            # weight_mask = TopKBinarizer.apply(score,1 - self.cfg.NASConfig['PruningRatio'])  # pruning at running
 467            bias_mask = weight_mask
 468            weight_mask = torch.unsqueeze(weight_mask, 1) * torch.ones(self._module_instance.weight.shape[1],
 469                                                                       device=weight_mask.device)
 470
 471            # weight and bias is not changed but score tensor is attached to the computational graph
 472            masked_weight = self._module_instance.weight * weight_mask
 473            masked_bias = self._module_instance.bias * bias_mask
 474            return F.linear(x, masked_weight, masked_bias)
 475        else:
 476            return self._module_instance(x)
 477
 478    @staticmethod
 479    def identity_module(cfg, name, input_shape: tuple):
 480        if type(name) != str:
 481            name = cfg.NASConfig['editable'][name]
 482        module = DenseModule(cfg, name, input_shape)
 483        dense = nn.Linear(input_shape[-1], input_shape[-1], bias=True)
 484        dense.weight = nn.Parameter(torch.eye(input_shape[-1]))
 485        dense.bias = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(input_shape[-1]))
 486        module.current_level = input_shape[1]
 487        module.output_shape = input_shape
 488        module.params = {'in_features': input_shape[1], 'out_features': input_shape[1]}
 489        module._module_instance = dense
 490        # add pruning field
 491        if cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 492            module.importance_score = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(module.current_level))
 493        return module
 494
 495    def get_module_instance(self):
 496        if self._module_instance is not None:
 497            return self._module_instance
 498        self._module_instance = nn.Linear(self.params['in_features'], self.params['out_features'], bias=True)
 499        return self._module_instance
 500
 501    @property
 502    def token(self):
 503        return 'dense-%d' % (self.params['out_features'])
 504
 505    def perform_wider_transformation_current(self):
 506        next_level = self.next_level
 507        new_module_instance = nn.Linear(self.params['in_features'], next_level)
 508        # keep previous parameters
 509        mapping_g = self.widen_sample_fn(self.current_level, next_level)
 510        scale_g = [1 / mapping_g.count(i) for i in mapping_g]
 511        new_module_instance.bias = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.bias[mapping_g])
 512        new_module_instance.weight = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.weight[mapping_g])
 513        self.current_level = next_level
 514        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 515        self.output_shape = (self.output_shape[0], self.current_level)
 516        self.params['out_features'] = self.current_level
 517        if self.cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 518            self.importance_score = Parameter(self.importance_score[mapping_g])
 519        return mapping_g, scale_g
 520
 521    def perform_wider_transformation_next(self, mapping_g: list, scale_g: list):
 522        next_level = len(mapping_g)
 523        scale_g = torch.tensor(scale_g)
 524        new_module_instance = nn.Linear(next_level, self.params['out_features'])
 525        # keep previous parameters
 526        new_module_instance.weight = nn.Parameter(
 527            self._module_instance.weight[:, mapping_g] * scale_g.unsqueeze(0))
 528        new_module_instance.bias = nn.Parameter(
 529            self._module_instance.bias)
 530        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 531        self.input_shape = (self.input_shape[0], next_level)
 532        self.params['in_features'] = next_level
 533
 534
 535class ConvModule(NasModule):
 536    def perform_prune_current(self, mask):
 537        """
 538        prune conv layer by feature maps, inplace operation
 539        :param mask: mask of pruning, should be equal to out channels of module
 540        """
 541        self.mask_sanity_check(mask)  # ensure mask legal
 542        self.current_level = mask.sum().item()
 543        new_module_instance = nn.Conv1d(in_channels=self.params['in_channels'],
 544                                        out_channels=self.current_level,
 545                                        kernel_size=self.params['kernel_size'],
 546                                        stride=self.params['stride'],
 547                                        padding=self.params['padding'])
 548
 549        # assigning new attribute
 550        new_module_instance.bias = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.bias[mask])
 551        new_module_instance.weight = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.weight[mask])
 552        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 553        self.output_shape = (self.output_shape[0], self.current_level)
 554        self.params['out_channels'] = self.current_level
 555        self.importance_score = nn.Parameter(self.importance_score[mask])
 556
 557    def perform_prune_next(self, mask):
 558        self.params['in_channels'] = mask.sum().item()
 559        new_module_instance = nn.Conv1d(in_channels=self.params['in_channels'],
 560                                        out_channels=self.params['out_channels'],
 561                                        kernel_size=self.params['kernel_size'],
 562                                        stride=self.params['stride'], padding=self.params['padding'])
 563        new_module_instance.weight = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.weight[:, mask])
 564        new_module_instance.bias = self._module_instance.bias
 565
 566        # assigning new attribute
 567        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 568        self.input_shape = (self.input_shape[0], self.params['in_channels'])
 569
 570    @property
 571    def is_max_level(self):
 572        out_range = self.cfg.modulesConfig['conv']['out_range']
 573        return self.current_level >= max(out_range)
 574
 575    def init_param(self, input_shape, max_width):
 576        assert len(input_shape) == 2
 577        self.params = {'in_channels': input_shape[1]}
 578        out_range = self.cfg.modulesConfig['conv']['out_range']
 579        self.current_level = self.get_level(out_range, max_width)
 580        self.params['out_channels'] = self.current_level
 581        self.params['kernel_size'] = 3
 582        self.params['stride'] = 1
 583        self.params['padding'] = 1
 584        self.on_param_end(input_shape[::-1])
 585        self.output_shape = self.output_shape[::-1]
 586        # add pruning field
 587        if self.cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 588            self.importance_score = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(self.current_level))
 589
 590    def forward(self, x):
 591        x = x.permute(0, 2, 1)
 592        if self.cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 593            assert self.importance_score is not None
 594            # accumulate importance score of whole row, we use this as importance estimation of output neuron
 595            score = self.importance_score
 596            weight_mask = ScoreAccumulator.apply(score)  # no change
 597            # weight_mask = TopKBinarizer.apply(score,1 - self.cfg.NASConfig['PruningRatio'])  # pruning at running
 598            bias_mask = weight_mask
 599
 600            # weight and bias is not changed but score tensor is attached to the computational graph
 601            masked_weight = self._module_instance.weight * torch.unsqueeze(torch.unsqueeze(weight_mask, 1), 1)
 602            masked_bias = self._module_instance.bias * bias_mask
 603            y = F.conv1d(x, masked_weight, masked_bias, self._module_instance.stride,
 604                         self._module_instance.padding)
 605        else:
 606            y = self._module_instance(x)
 607        y = y.permute(0, 2, 1)
 608        return y
 609
 610    @staticmethod
 611    def identity_module(cfg, name, input_shape: tuple):
 612        if type(name) != str:
 613            name = cfg.NASConfig['editable'][name]
 614        module = ConvModule(cfg, name, input_shape)
 615        out_channel = input_shape[1]
 616        in_channel = input_shape[1]
 617        kernel_size = 3
 618        module.current_level = out_channel
 619        module.output_shape = input_shape
 620        module.params = {
 621            "in_channels": in_channel,
 622            "out_channels": out_channel,
 623            "kernel_size": kernel_size,
 624            "stride": 1,
 625            "padding": 1,
 626        }
 627        conv = nn.Conv1d(in_channels=module.params['in_channels'],
 628                         out_channels=module.params['out_channels'],
 629                         kernel_size=module.params['kernel_size'],
 630                         stride=module.params['stride'],
 631                         padding=module.params['padding'])
 632        weight = torch.zeros((out_channel, in_channel, kernel_size))
 633        for i in range(in_channel):
 634            weight[i, i, 1] = 1
 635        conv.weight = nn.Parameter(weight)
 636        bias = torch.zeros(out_channel)
 637        conv.bias = nn.Parameter(bias)
 638        module._module_instance = conv
 639        if cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 640            module.importance_score = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(module.current_level))
 641        return module
 642
 643    def get_module_instance(self):
 644        if self._module_instance is not None:
 645            return self._module_instance
 646        self._module_instance = nn.Conv1d(
 647            in_channels=self.params['in_channels'],
 648            out_channels=self.params['out_channels'],
 649            kernel_size=self.params['kernel_size'],
 650            stride=self.params['stride'],
 651            padding=self.params['padding'])
 652        return self._module_instance
 653
 654    @property
 655    def token(self):
 656        return 'conv-%d' % (self.params['out_channels'])
 657
 658    def perform_wider_transformation_current(self):
 659        next_level = self.next_level
 660        new_module_instance = nn.Conv1d(in_channels=self.params['in_channels'],
 661                                        out_channels=self.next_level,
 662                                        kernel_size=self.params['kernel_size'],
 663                                        stride=self.params['stride'],
 664                                        padding=self.params['padding'])
 665        # keep previous parameters
 666        mapping_g = self.widen_sample_fn(self.current_level, next_level)
 667        scale_g = [1 / mapping_g.count(i) for i in mapping_g]
 668        new_module_instance.bias = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.bias[mapping_g])
 669        new_module_instance.weight = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.weight[mapping_g])
 670        self.current_level = next_level
 671        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 672        self.output_shape = (self.output_shape[0], self.current_level)
 673        self.params['out_channels'] = self.current_level
 674        if self.cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 675            self.importance_score = Parameter(self.importance_score[mapping_g])
 676        return mapping_g, scale_g
 677
 678    def perform_wider_transformation_next(self, mapping_g: list, scale_g: list):
 679        next_level = len(mapping_g)
 680        scale_g = torch.tensor(scale_g)
 681        new_module_instance = nn.Conv1d(in_channels=next_level,
 682                                        out_channels=self.params['out_channels'],
 683                                        kernel_size=self.params['kernel_size'],
 684                                        stride=self.params['stride'], padding=self.params['padding'])
 685        new_module_instance.weight = \
 686            nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.weight[:, mapping_g] *
 687                         scale_g.unsqueeze(0).unsqueeze(2), )
 688        new_module_instance.bias = self._module_instance.bias
 689        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 690        self.params['in_channels'] = next_level
 691        self.input_shape = (self.input_shape[0], self.params['in_channels'])

 694class LSTMModule(NasModule):
 695    def perform_prune_current(self, mask):
 696        """
 697        prune rnn layer by output neuron
 698        @param mask:
 699        """
 700        self.mask_sanity_check(mask)  # ensure mask legal
 701        self.current_level = mask.sum().item()
 702        new_module_instance = NAS_SLSTM(self.params['input_size'], self.current_level)
 703
 704        # keep previous parameters
 705        new_module_instance.cell.weight_ih = nn.Parameter(
 706            torch.cat(tuple(map(lambda x: x[:, mask], self._module_instance.cell.weight_ih.chunk(4, 1))), dim=1))
 707        new_module_instance.cell.weight_hh = nn.Parameter(
 708            torch.cat(tuple(map(lambda x: x[mask][:, mask], self._module_instance.cell.weight_hh.chunk(4, 1))), dim=1))
 709        new_module_instance.cell.bias_ih = nn.Parameter(
 710            torch.cat(tuple(map(lambda x: x[mask], self._module_instance.cell.bias_ih.chunk(4)))))
 711
 712        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 713        self.output_shape = (self.output_shape[0], self.current_level)
 714        self.params['output_size'] = self.current_level
 715        self.importance_score = nn.Parameter(self.importance_score[mask])
 716
 717    def perform_prune_next(self, mask):
 718        input_size = mask.sum().item()
 719        new_module_instance = NAS_SLSTM(input_size, self.params['output_size'])
 720        new_module_instance.cell.weight_ih = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.cell.weight_ih[mask])
 721        new_module_instance.cell.weight_hh = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.cell.weight_hh)
 722        new_module_instance.cell.bias_ih = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.cell.bias_ih)
 723
 724        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 725
 726        self.input_shape = (self.input_shape[0], input_size)
 727        self.params['input_size'] = input_size
 728
 729    @property
 730    def is_max_level(self):
 731        out_range = self.cfg.modulesConfig['lstm']['out_range']
 732        return self.current_level >= max(out_range)
 733
 734
 735    def init_param(self, input_shape, max_width):
 736        assert len(input_shape) == 2
 737        self.params = dict()
 738        out_range = self.cfg.modulesConfig['lstm']['out_range']
 739        self.current_level = self.get_level(out_range, max_width)
 740        self.params['input_size'] = input_shape[1]
 741        self.params['output_size'] = self.current_level
 742        self.on_param_end(input_shape)
 743        self.output_shape = self.output_shape
 744        # add pruning field
 745        if self.cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 746            self.importance_score = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(self.current_level))
 747            clip_threshold = 1e6
 748
 749            def accumulate_importance(score):
 750                if self.importance_score.grad is None:
 751                    self.importance_score.grad = score
 752                else:
 753                    self.importance_score.grad += score
 754
 755            def weight_ih_accumulate(grad):
 756                # add gradient clip to avoid gradient exploding
 757                grad = torch.clip(grad, -clip_threshold, clip_threshold)
 758                weight = self._module_instance.cell.weight_ih
 759                grad_calculated = torch.sum(weight * grad, 0)
 760                grad_calculated = sum(grad_calculated.chunk(4))
 761                accumulate_importance(grad_calculated)
 762                return grad
 763
 764            def weight_hh_accumulate(grad):
 765                grad = torch.clip(grad, -clip_threshold, clip_threshold)
 766                weight = self._module_instance.cell.weight_hh
 767                grad_calculated = weight * grad
 768                gates = grad_calculated.chunk(4, 1)
 769                grad_calculated = sum(map(lambda x: torch.sum(x, 0), gates)) + sum(
 770                    map(lambda x: torch.sum(x, 1), gates))
 771                accumulate_importance(grad_calculated)
 772                return grad
 773
 774            def bias_ih_accumulate(grad):
 775                grad = torch.clip(grad, -clip_threshold, clip_threshold)
 776                weight = self._module_instance.cell.bias_ih
 777                grad_calculated = weight * grad
 778                grad_calculated = sum(grad_calculated.chunk(4))
 779                accumulate_importance(grad_calculated)
 780                return grad
 781
 782            self._module_instance.cell.weight_ih.register_hook(weight_ih_accumulate)
 783            self._module_instance.cell.weight_hh.register_hook(weight_hh_accumulate)
 784            self._module_instance.cell.bias_ih.register_hook(bias_ih_accumulate)
 785
 786    def forward(self, x):
 787        return self.get_module_instance()(x)
 788
 789    @staticmethod
 790    def identity_module(cfg, name, input_shape: tuple):
 791        if type(name) != str:
 792            name = cfg.NASConfig['editable'][name]
 793        module = LSTMModule(cfg, name, input_shape)
 794        hidden_size = input_shape[1]
 795        input_size = input_shape[1]
 796        module.params = {
 797            "output_size": hidden_size,
 798            "input_size": input_size,
 799        }
 800        module.current_level = hidden_size
 801        module.output_shape = input_shape
 802        identity_lstm = NAS_SLSTM.generate_identity(input_size)
 803        module._module_instance = identity_lstm
 804        if cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 805            module.importance_score = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(module.current_level))
 806        return module
 807
 808    def get_module_instance(self):
 809        if self._module_instance is not None:
 810            return self._module_instance
 811        self._module_instance = NAS_SLSTM(
 812            input_size=self.params['input_size'],
 813            hidden_size=self.params['output_size'],
 814        )
 815        # if not isinstance(self._module_instance,torch.jit.RecursiveScriptModule):
 816        #     self._module_instance = torch.jit.script(self._module_instance)
 817        return self._module_instance
 818
 819    @property
 820    def token(self):
 821        return 'lstm-%d' % (self.params['output_size'])
 822
 823    def perform_wider_transformation_current(self):
 824        next_level = self.next_level
 825        new_module_instance = NAS_SLSTM(self.params['input_size'], next_level)
 826        # keep previous parameters
 827        mapping_g = self.widen_sample_fn(self.current_level, next_level)
 828        scale_g = [1 / mapping_g.count(i) for i in mapping_g]
 829        scale_g = torch.tensor(scale_g)
 830        new_module_instance.cell.weight_ih = nn.Parameter(
 831            torch.cat(tuple(map(lambda x: x[:, mapping_g], self._module_instance.cell.weight_ih.chunk(4, 1))), dim=1))
 832        new_module_instance.cell.weight_hh = nn.Parameter(torch.cat(tuple(
 833            map(lambda x: x[mapping_g][:, mapping_g] * torch.unsqueeze(scale_g, 1),
 834                self._module_instance.cell.weight_hh.chunk(4, 1))), dim=1))
 835        new_module_instance.cell.bias_ih = nn.Parameter(
 836            torch.cat(tuple(map(lambda x: x[mapping_g], self._module_instance.cell.bias_ih.chunk(4)))))
 837        self.current_level = next_level
 838        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 839        self.output_shape = (self.output_shape[0], self.current_level)
 840        self.params['output_size'] = self.current_level
 841        if self.cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 842            self.importance_score = Parameter(self.importance_score[mapping_g])
 843        return mapping_g, scale_g
 844
 845    def perform_wider_transformation_next(self, mapping_g: list, scale_g: list):
 846        next_level = len(mapping_g)
 847        scale_g = torch.tensor(scale_g)
 848        new_module_instance = NAS_SLSTM(next_level, self.params['output_size'])
 849        new_module_instance.cell.weight_ih = nn.Parameter(
 850            self._module_instance.cell.weight_ih[mapping_g] * torch.unsqueeze(scale_g, 1))
 851        new_module_instance.cell.weight_hh = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.cell.weight_hh)
 852        new_module_instance.cell.bias_ih = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.cell.bias_ih)
 853        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
 854        self.input_shape = (self.input_shape[0], next_level)
 855        self.params['input_size'] = next_level

 858# this class comes from [Movement Pruning](https://github.com/huggingface/nn_pruning)
 859class TopK(autograd.Function):
 860    """
 861    Top-k Binarizer.
 862    Computes a binary mask M from a real value matrix S such that `M_{i,j} = 1` if and only if `S_{i,j}`
 863    is among the k% highest values of S.
 864
 865    Implementation is inspired from:
 866        https://github.com/allenai/hidden-networks
 867        What's hidden in a randomly weighted neural network?
 868        Vivek Ramanujan*, Mitchell Wortsman*, Aniruddha Kembhavi, Ali Farhadi, Mohammad Rastegari
 869    """
 870
 871    @staticmethod
 872    def forward(ctx, inputs: torch.tensor, threshold: float):
 873        """
 874        Args:
 875            inputs (`torch.FloatTensor`)
 876                The input matrix from which the binarizer computes the binary mask.
 877            threshold (`float`)
 878                The percentage of weights to keep (the rest is pruned).
 879                `threshold` is a float between 0 and 1.
 880        Returns:
 881            mask (`torch.FloatTensor`)
 882                Binary matrix of the same size as `inputs` acting as a mask (1 - the associated weight is
 883                retained, 0 - the associated weight is pruned).
 884        """
 885        # Get the subnetwork by sorting the inputs and using the top threshold %
 886        mask = inputs.clone()
 887        _, idx = inputs.flatten().sort(descending=True)
 888        j = int(threshold * inputs.numel())
 889
 890        # flat_out and mask access the same memory.
 891        flat_out = mask.flatten()
 892        flat_out[idx[j:]] = 0
 893        flat_out[idx[:j]] = 1
 894        return mask == 1
 895
 896    @staticmethod
 897    def backward(ctx, gradOutput):
 898        return gradOutput, None
 899

 901# Implementation inspired by TopKBinarizer
 902class ScoreAccumulator(autograd.Function):
 903    """
 904    Accumulate importance score while training. Do not change forward data
 905    """
 906
 907    @staticmethod
 908    def forward(ctx, score):
 909        return torch.ones_like(score, device=score.device)
 910
 911    @staticmethod
 912    def backward(ctx, gradOutput):
 913        return gradOutput, None

 928class LSTMCell(nn.Module):
 929    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size):
 930        super(LSTMCell, self).__init__()
 931        self.input_size = input_size
 932        self.hidden_size = hidden_size
 933        self.weight_ih = Parameter(torch.randn(input_size, 4 * hidden_size))
 934        self.weight_hh = Parameter(torch.randn(hidden_size, 4 * hidden_size))
 935        self.bias_ih = Parameter(torch.randn(4 * hidden_size))
 936
 937    def forward(self, input: Tensor, h, c):
 938        hx, cx = h, c
 939        gates = (torch.mm(input, self.weight_ih) + self.bias_ih +
 940                 torch.mm(hx, self.weight_hh))
 941        ingate, forgetgate, cellgate, outgate = gates.chunk(4, 1)
 942
 943        ingate = torch.sigmoid(ingate)
 944        forgetgate = torch.sigmoid(forgetgate)
 945        cellgate = torch.tanh(cellgate)
 946        outgate = outgate
 947
 948        cy = (forgetgate * cx) + (ingate * cellgate)
 949        hy = outgate * torch.tanh(cy) + outgate
 950
 951        return hy, cy
 952
 953
 954class NAS_SLSTM(nn.Module):
 955
 956    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size):
 957        super().__init__()
 958        self.hidden_size = hidden_size
 959        self.input_size = input_size
 960        self.cell = LSTMCell(input_size, hidden_size)
 961        self.reset_parameters()
 962
 963    def reset_parameters(self) -> None:
 964        """
 965        follow implementation with pytorch
 966        """
 967        stdv = 1.0 / math.sqrt(self.hidden_size) if self.hidden_size > 0 else 0
 968        for weight in self.parameters():
 969            init.uniform_(weight, -stdv, stdv)
 970
 971    def forward(self, x):
 972        """
 973        forward propagation
 974        @param x:  input of size [batch, seqlen, feature]
 975        @return: hidden state [batch, seqlen, feature]
 976        """
 977        h = torch.zeros((x.shape[0], self.hidden_size), device=x.device)
 978        c = torch.zeros((x.shape[0], self.hidden_size), device=x.device)
 979        input = x.unbind(1)
 980        outputs = []
 981        for i in range(len(input)):
 982            h, c = self.cell(input[i], h, c)
 983            outputs += [h]
 984        output = torch.stack(outputs, 1)
 985        return output
 986
 987    @staticmethod
 988    def generate_identity(input_size):
 989        lstm = NAS_SLSTM(input_size, input_size)
 990        weight_ih = torch.zeros_like(lstm.cell.weight_ih)
 991        weight_ih[:, 3 * input_size:] = torch.eye(input_size)
 992        lstm.cell.weight_ih = nn.Parameter(weight_ih)
 993        lstm.cell.weight_hh = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros_like(lstm.cell.weight_hh))
 994        lstm.cell.bias_ih = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros_like(lstm.cell.bias_ih))
 995        return lstm

 998def generate_module(cfg, name, input_shape) -> NasModule:
 999    """
1000    generate module instance, this function binding module name to exact module class
1001    :param cfg: global configuration
1002    :param name: name of module
1003    :param input_shape: input tensor shape
1004    :return: subclass of NAS_Module corresponding to name
1005    """
1006    if name in cfg.modulesCls:
1007        return cfg.modulesCls[name](cfg, name, input_shape)
1008    else:
1009        raise RuntimeError(f'no such module {name}, please if the module is not registered')

1012def generate_from_skeleton(cfg, skeleton: list, input_shape, max_width):
1013    """
1014    generate a list of module instance from skeleton list
1015    :param cfg: global configuration
1016    :param skeleton: skeleton list of string specifying each layer's type
1017    :param input_shape: input data shape
1018    :param max_width: max width of neural layer
1019    :return: list of modules
1020    """
1021    modules = []
1022    for name in skeleton + ['dense']:
1023        module = generate_module(cfg, name, input_shape)
1024        try:
1025            module.init_param(input_shape, max_width)
1026            input_shape = module.output_shape
1027            modules.append(module)
1028        except Exception as e:
1029            logger = get_logger('module init', cfg.LOG_FILE)
1030            logger.error(f'fail to init module {module},\n'
1031                         f' {"message".center(50, "=")}\n'
1032                         f'{e}'
1033                         f'{"end".center(50, "=")}')
1034    return modules
class NasModule(torch.nn.modules.module.Module): 
 17class NasModule(nn.Module):
 18    def __init__(self, cfg, name: str, input_shape):
 19        """
 20        basic module composing neural networks.
 21        :param cfg: global configuration
 22        :param name: module name
 23        :param input_shape: input data shape
 24        """
 25        super().__init__()
 26        self.logger = get_logger('module', cfg.LOG_FILE)
 27        self.cfg = cfg
 28        self.input_shape = input_shape  # (channel, feature)
 29        self.name = name
 30        self.output_shape = None
 31        self.params = None
 32        self.editable = self.cfg.modulesConfig[name]['editable']
 33        self._module_instance = None  # buffer the instance
 34        self.current_level = None  # current width level
 35        self.widen_sample_fn = self.default_sample_strategy
 36        # add pruning field
 37        if cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
 38            self.importance_score = None  # importance score matrix

174    @staticmethod

176        """
177        default sample strategy described in paper
178        :param original_size: original layer width
179        :param new_size: new layer width, we have new_size >original_size
180        :return: sampling sequence
181        """
182        seq = list(range(original_size))
183        num_to_sample = new_size - original_size
184        while num_to_sample != 0:
185            sample_number = min(original_size, num_to_sample)
186            seq += random.sample(seq, sample_number)
187            num_to_sample = num_to_sample - sample_number
188        return seq

Base class for all neural network modules.

Your models should also subclass this class.

Modules can also contain other Modules, allowing to nest them in a tree structure. You can assign the submodules as regular attributes::

import torch.nn as nn
import torch.nn.functional as F

class Model(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(1, 20, 5)
        self.conv2 = nn.Conv2d(20, 20, 5)

    def forward(self, x):
        x = F.relu(self.conv1(x))
        return F.relu(self.conv2(x))

Submodules assigned in this way will be registered, and will have their parameters converted too when you call to(), etc.

As per the example above, an __init__() call to the parent class must be made before assignment on the child.

:ivar training: Boolean represents whether this module is in training or evaluation mode. :vartype training: bool

import torch.nn as nn

class Model(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(1, 20, 5)
        self.conv2 = nn.Conv2d(20, 20, 5)

    def forward(self, x):

        return F.relu(self.conv2(x))

510        mapping_g = self.widen_sample_fn(self.current_level, next_level)
511        scale_g = [1 / mapping_g.count(i) for i in mapping_g]
512        new_module_instance.bias = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.bias[mapping_g])
513        new_module_instance.weight = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.weight[mapping_g])
514        self.current_level = next_level
515        self._module_instance = new_module_instance
516        self.output_shape = (self.output_shape[0], self.current_level)
517        self.params['out_features'] = self.current_level
518        if self.cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
519            self.importance_score = Parameter(self.importance_score[mapping_g])
520        return mapping_g, scale_g

591    def forward(self, x):
592        x = x.permute(0, 2, 1)
593        if self.cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
594            assert self.importance_score is not None
595            # accumulate importance score of whole row, we use this as importance estimation of output neuron
596            score = self.importance_score
597            weight_mask = ScoreAccumulator.apply(score)  # no change
598            # weight_mask = TopKBinarizer.apply(score,1 - self.cfg.NASConfig['PruningRatio'])  # pruning at running
599            bias_mask = weight_mask
600
601            # weight and bias is not changed but score tensor is attached to the computational graph
602            masked_weight = self._module_instance.weight * torch.unsqueeze(torch.unsqueeze(weight_mask, 1), 1)
603            masked_bias = self._module_instance.bias * bias_mask
604            y = F.conv1d(x, masked_weight, masked_bias, self._module_instance.stride,
605                         self._module_instance.padding)
606        else:
607            y = self._module_instance(x)
608        y = y.permute(0, 2, 1)
609        return y

Base class for all neural network modules.

Your models should also subclass this class.

Modules can also contain other Modules, allowing to nest them in a tree structure. You can assign the submodules as regular attributes::

import torch.nn as nn
import torch.nn.functional as F

class Model(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(1, 20, 5)
        self.conv2 = nn.Conv2d(20, 20, 5)

    def forward(self, x):
        x = F.relu(self.conv1(x))
        return F.relu(self.conv2(x))

Submodules assigned in this way will be registered, and will have their parameters converted too when you call to(), etc.

As per the example above, an __init__() call to the parent class must be made before assignment on the child.

696    def perform_prune_current(self, mask):
697        """
698        prune rnn layer by output neuron
699        @param mask:
700        """
701        self.mask_sanity_check(mask)  # ensure mask legal
702        self.current_level = mask.sum().item()
703        new_module_instance = NAS_SLSTM(self.params['input_size'], self.current_level)
704
705        # keep previous parameters
706        new_module_instance.cell.weight_ih = nn.Parameter(
707            torch.cat(tuple(map(lambda x: x[:, mask], self._module_instance.cell.weight_ih.chunk(4, 1))), dim=1))

709            torch.cat(tuple(map(lambda x: x[mask][:, mask], self._module_instance.cell.weight_hh.chunk(4, 1))), dim=1))

722        new_module_instance.cell.weight_hh = nn.Parameter(self._module_instance.cell.weight_hh)

736    def init_param(self, input_shape, max_width):
737        assert len(input_shape) == 2
738        self.params = dict()
739        out_range = self.cfg.modulesConfig['lstm']['out_range']
740        self.current_level = self.get_level(out_range, max_width)
741        self.params['input_size'] = input_shape[1]
742        self.params['output_size'] = self.current_level
743        self.on_param_end(input_shape)
744        self.output_shape = self.output_shape
745        # add pruning field
746        if self.cfg.NASConfig['Pruning']:
747            self.importance_score = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(self.current_level))
748            clip_threshold = 1e6
749
750            def accumulate_importance(score):
751                if self.importance_score.grad is None:
752                    self.importance_score.grad = score
753                else:
754                    self.importance_score.grad += score
755
756            def weight_ih_accumulate(grad):
757                # add gradient clip to avoid gradient exploding
758                grad = torch.clip(grad, -clip_threshold, clip_threshold)
759                weight = self._module_instance.cell.weight_ih
760                grad_calculated = torch.sum(weight * grad, 0)
761                grad_calculated = sum(grad_calculated.chunk(4))
762                accumulate_importance(grad_calculated)
763                return grad
764
765            def weight_hh_accumulate(grad):
766                grad = torch.clip(grad, -clip_threshold, clip_threshold)
767                weight = self._module_instance.cell.weight_hh
768                grad_calculated = weight * grad
769                gates = grad_calculated.chunk(4, 1)
770                grad_calculated = sum(map(lambda x: torch.sum(x, 0), gates)) + sum(
771                    map(lambda x: torch.sum(x, 1), gates))
772                accumulate_importance(grad_calculated)
773                return grad
774
775            def bias_ih_accumulate(grad):
776                grad = torch.clip(grad, -clip_threshold, clip_threshold)
777                weight = self._module_instance.cell.bias_ih
778                grad_calculated = weight * grad
779                grad_calculated = sum(grad_calculated.chunk(4))
780                accumulate_importance(grad_calculated)
781                return grad
782
783            self._module_instance.cell.weight_ih.register_hook(weight_ih_accumulate)
784            self._module_instance.cell.weight_hh.register_hook(weight_hh_accumulate)
785            self._module_instance.cell.bias_ih.register_hook(bias_ih_accumulate)
786

788        return self.get_module_instance()(x)

747            self.importance_score = nn.Parameter(torch.zeros(self.current_level))
748            clip_threshold = 1e6
749
750            def accumulate_importance(score):
751                if self.importance_score.grad is None:
752                    self.importance_score.grad = score
753                else:
754                    self.importance_score.grad += score
755
756            def weight_ih_accumulate(grad):
757                # add gradient clip to avoid gradient exploding
758                grad = torch.clip(grad, -clip_threshold, clip_threshold)
759                weight = self._module_instance.cell.weight_ih
760                grad_calculated = torch.sum(weight * grad, 0)
761                grad_calculated = sum(grad_calculated.chunk(4))
762                accumulate_importance(grad_calculated)
763                return grad
764
765            def weight_hh_accumulate(grad):
766                grad = torch.clip(grad, -clip_threshold, clip_threshold)
767                weight = self._module_instance.cell.weight_hh
768                grad_calculated = weight * grad
769                gates = grad_calculated.chunk(4, 1)
770                grad_calculated = sum(map(lambda x: torch.sum(x, 0), gates)) + sum(
771                    map(lambda x: torch.sum(x, 1), gates))
772                accumulate_importance(grad_calculated)
773                return grad
774
775            def bias_ih_accumulate(grad):
776                grad = torch.clip(grad, -clip_threshold, clip_threshold)
777                weight = self._module_instance.cell.bias_ih
778                grad_calculated = weight * grad
779                grad_calculated = sum(grad_calculated.chunk(4))
780                accumulate_importance(grad_calculated)
781                return grad
782
783            self._module_instance.cell.weight_ih.register_hook(weight_ih_accumulate)
784            self._module_instance.cell.weight_hh.register_hook(weight_hh_accumulate)
785            self._module_instance.cell.bias_ih.register_hook(bias_ih_accumulate)

class TopK(torch.autograd.function.Function): 
860class TopK(autograd.Function):
861    """
862    Top-k Binarizer.
863    Computes a binary mask M from a real value matrix S such that `M_{i,j} = 1` if and only if `S_{i,j}`
864    is among the k% highest values of S.
865
866    Implementation is inspired from:
867        https://github.com/allenai/hidden-networks
868        What's hidden in a randomly weighted neural network?
869        Vivek Ramanujan*, Mitchell Wortsman*, Aniruddha Kembhavi, Ali Farhadi, Mohammad Rastegari
870    """
871
872    @staticmethod
873    def forward(ctx, inputs: torch.tensor, threshold: float):
874        """
875        Args:
876            inputs (`torch.FloatTensor`)
877                The input matrix from which the binarizer computes the binary mask.
878            threshold (`float`)
879                The percentage of weights to keep (the rest is pruned).
880                `threshold` is a float between 0 and 1.
881        Returns:
882            mask (`torch.FloatTensor`)
883                Binary matrix of the same size as `inputs` acting as a mask (1 - the associated weight is
884                retained, 0 - the associated weight is pruned).
885        """
886        # Get the subnetwork by sorting the inputs and using the top threshold %
887        mask = inputs.clone()
888        _, idx = inputs.flatten().sort(descending=True)
889        j = int(threshold * inputs.numel())
890
891        # flat_out and mask access the same memory.
892        flat_out = mask.flatten()
893        flat_out[idx[j:]] = 0
894        flat_out[idx[:j]] = 1
895        return mask == 1
896
897    @staticmethod
898    def backward(ctx, gradOutput):
899        return gradOutput, None

Defines a formula for differentiating the operation with backward mode automatic differentiation (alias to the vjp function).

This function is to be overridden by all subclasses.

It must accept a context ctx as the first argument, followed by as many outputs as the forward() returned (None will be passed in for non tensor outputs of the forward function), and it should return as many tensors, as there were inputs to forward(). Each argument is the gradient w.r.t the given output, and each returned value should be the gradient w.r.t. the corresponding input. If an input is not a Tensor or is a Tensor not requiring grads, you can just pass None as a gradient for that input.

The context can be used to retrieve tensors saved during the forward pass. It also has an attribute ctx.needs_input_grad as a tuple of booleans representing whether each input needs gradient. E.g., backward() will have ctx.needs_input_grad[0] = True if the first input to forward() needs gradient computated w.r.t. the output.

class LSTMCell(torch.nn.modules.module.Module): 
929class LSTMCell(nn.Module):
930    def __init__(self, input_size, hidden_size):
931        super(LSTMCell, self).__init__()
932        self.input_size = input_size
933        self.hidden_size = hidden_size
934        self.weight_ih = Parameter(torch.randn(input_size, 4 * hidden_size))
935        self.weight_hh = Parameter(torch.randn(hidden_size, 4 * hidden_size))
936        self.bias_ih = Parameter(torch.randn(4 * hidden_size))
937
938    def forward(self, input: Tensor, h, c):
939        hx, cx = h, c
940        gates = (torch.mm(input, self.weight_ih) + self.bias_ih +
941                 torch.mm(hx, self.weight_hh))
942        ingate, forgetgate, cellgate, outgate = gates.chunk(4, 1)
943
944        ingate = torch.sigmoid(ingate)
945        forgetgate = torch.sigmoid(forgetgate)
946        cellgate = torch.tanh(cellgate)
947        outgate = outgate
948
949        cy = (forgetgate * cx) + (ingate * cellgate)
950        hy = outgate * torch.tanh(cy) + outgate

Base class for all neural network modules.

Your models should also subclass this class.

Modules can also contain other Modules, allowing to nest them in a tree structure. You can assign the submodules as regular attributes::

import torch.nn as nn
import torch.nn.functional as F

class Model(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()
        self.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(1, 20, 5)
        self.conv2 = nn.Conv2d(20, 20, 5)

    def forward(self, x):
        x = F.relu(self.conv1(x))
        return F.relu(self.conv2(x))

Submodules assigned in this way will be registered, and will have their parameters converted too when you call to(), etc.

As per the example above, an __init__() call to the parent class must be made before assignment on the child.

:ivar training: Boolean represents whether this module is in training or evaluation mode. :vartype training: bool

Defines the computation performed at every call.

Should be overridden by all subclasses.

Although the recipe for forward pass needs to be defined within this function, one should call the Module instance afterwards instead of this since the former takes care of running the registered hooks while the latter silently ignores them.

964    def reset_parameters(self) -> None:
965        """
966        follow implementation with pytorch
967        """
968        stdv = 1.0 / math.sqrt(self.hidden_size) if self.hidden_size > 0 else 0
969        for weight in self.parameters():
970            init.uniform_(weight, -stdv, stdv)

972    def forward(self, x):
973        """
974        forward propagation
975        @param x:  input of size [batch, seqlen, feature]
976        @return: hidden state [batch, seqlen, feature]
977        """
978        h = torch.zeros((x.shape[0], self.hidden_size), device=x.device)
979        c = torch.zeros((x.shape[0], self.hidden_size), device=x.device)
980        input = x.unbind(1)
981        outputs = []

983            h, c = self.cell(input[i], h, c)
984            outputs += [h]
985        output = torch.stack(outputs, 1)
